<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-09-07T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-09-07T15:00:00-05:00" n="802" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d802">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">825.00 Revolutions/22: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-09-07T16:00:00-04:00">September 7, 1931—4
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 6 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>114. Navy Department states that it is in radio communication with the
                            battleship <hi rend="italic">Latorre</hi> and that it and the two
                            remaining mutinous ships have agreed to surrender. Details of surrender
                            not yet known.</p>
                        <p>Repeated Lima.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>